En las Maratones de Programacion el ideal, consiste en resolver la mayor cantidad de problemas en un tiempo dado, generalmente son 6 horas, en las que se plantean 8 problemas, algunos son codigo facil, como bucles repetitivos que hagan el calculo deseado
sin embargo hay que pensar antes de programar, todo fallo es penalizado, desde demoras en el codigo, hasta, respuestas incorrrectas, al momento de presentar un codigo este debe ser pensado y de debe tener la certeza de por que funciona
hay codigos que presentan mas de una solucion, sin embargo los codigos que son mas eficientes reciben bonificaciones, asi mismo no cualquiera puede presentar una solucion, pues mas que habilidad para programar, se requiere de habilidad para solucionar el problema.

In programming marathons, the ideal is to solve as many problems as possible within a given time, usually 6 hours, during which 8 problems are presented. Some are easy code, like repetitive loops that perform the desired calculation. However, you need to think before programming
every mistake is penalized, from delays in the code to incorrect answers. When presenting code, it must be well thought out, and you must be certain of why it works. There are codes that offer more than one solution, but the more efficient codes receive bonuses. Additionally, not just anyone can present a solution
more than programming skills, problem-solving skills are required.
